programme.title: Гречанка
programme.desc: Главная героиня - Таня Куликова работает экскурсоводом в небольшом провинциальном музее. Она серьезно интересуется искусством, а главный ее "конёк" – искусство Древней Греции. Таня и внешне похожа на гречанку – кареглазая, смуглая, с копной вьющихся волос. Именно благодаря своему увлечению, девушка знакомится с предприимчивым арт-дилером из Москвы – Григорием Середой. Он красив, богат, умен – настоящий принц. Казалось бы, главная героиня вытащила тот самый счастливый билет. Но только Таня и не догадывается, что, выйдя замуж за Гришу, ей придется иметь дело с его властной матерью, бесхребетной сестрой и интриганкой-любовницей. Сказка для Тани быстро сменится суровыми буднями. Но сможет ли девушка пройти нелегкий, полный предательства, разочарований и страданий путь? Найдет ли она дорогу к своему счастью?

programme.title: The Spectacular Now
programme.desc: Sutter Keely (Miles Teller) lives in the now. It's a good place for him. A high school senior, charming and self-possessed, he's the life of the party, loves his job at a men's clothing store, and has no plans for the future. A budding alcoholic, he's never far from his supersized, whisky-fortified Thirst Master cup. But after being dumped by his girlfriend, Sutter gets drunk and wakes up on a lawn with Aimee Finicky (Shailene Woodley) hovering over him. She's different: the "nice girl" who reads science fiction and doesn't have a boyfriend. While Aimee has dreams of a future, Sutter lives in the impressive delusion of a spectacular now, yet somehow, they're drawn together.

programme.title: Something Borrowed
programme.desc: Romantic comedy. Two friends from law school realise they have feelings for each other, which extend beyond friendship, but there is one obstacle in the way - he is marrying her best friend. After a series of encounters and one-night stands, the groom-to-be is forced to put his feelings aside by his father, who pressures him into doing the right thing for all concerned.

programme.title: The Measure of a Man
programme.desc: 51-year-old Thierry is unemployed. Between pointless re-training and repeated humiliations, times are more than difficult. Together with his wife, he tries to keep what's most important: their apartment and the education of their disabled son. He finally manages to get a job as a security guard in a supermarket.

programme.title: The Grand Seduction
programme.desc: Comedy. The future of a small harbour village depends on whether a young passer-by doctor will take up residence. So, the desperate villagers come up with a brilliant plan, in order to seduce the young visitor to stay permanently.

programme.title: The Electrical Life of Louis Wain
programme.desc: Benedict Cumberbatch and Claire Foy star in director and co-writer Will Sharpe's period biopic about the tragic life of cat-fancying illustrator Louis Wain, narrated by Olivia Colman. Louis Wain is never still because of the "dark, screaming hurricane of crippling anxieties" that plague his consciousness. This has many outward manifestations - most notably a prodigious ability for illustration. Wain manages to provide for a household of women - his eccentric mother (Phoebe Nicholls) and five "hungry and precocious sisters" (Andrea Riseborough, Sharon Rooney, Aimee Lou Wood, Hayley Squires, Stacy Martin). Financially, this is largely due to accommodating magazine editor Sir William Ingram (Toby Jones), who recognises Wain's talent and tries his best to overlook the eccentricity. Wain's emotional life is transformed when Emily (Claire Foy) comes to work as governess to the girls. They fall deeply in love with one another. But Victorian society shuns them because of Emily's age and class. So they move to a quiet house in the country and are adopted by a stray cat called Peter. Emily says that cats are "ridiculous, silly, cuddly, frightened and brave, just like us" and the seeds are sewn. When Emily contracts breast cancer and becomes seriously ill, Louis starts drawing anthropomorphised cats to comfort her. These drawings make Louis famous and should have made him permanently rich. But without Emily to quiet the "dark, screaming hurricane" the future starts to unravel... Also featuring Nick Cave - a keen admirer and collector of Wain's cat paintings - as HG Wells. Co-written by Simon Stephenson. Produced by Benedict Cumberbatch. Network Premiere.

programme.title: What's Love Got to Do with It?
programme.desc: In London, an award-winning film-maker documents her best friend's journey into an assisted marriage in line with his family's Pakistani heritage. In the process, she challenges her own attitude towards relationships.

programme.title: Moonrise Kingdom
programme.desc: Jared Gilman and Kara Hayward star alongside Bruce Willis, Edward Norton, Bill Murray and Frances McDormand in Wes Anderson's coming-of-age comedy-drama about a pair of smitten 12-year-olds. It's 1965 and Sam (Gilman) is attending the Camp Ivanhoe scout camp on the New England island of New Penzance. While on the island the previous year, Sam met Suzy (Hayward) at an am-dram performance of Benjamin Britten's Noye's Fludde; in the interim they've become penfriends and have fallen in love. Now they plan to run away together to a secluded bay they've called Moonrise Kingdom. And that's what they do. But it's not long before her parents (Murray and McDormand), the local police captain (Willis), the scoutmaster (Norton) and the fearsome woman from Social Services (Tilda Swinton) have set out in pursuit of the sweethearts. That would be bad enough for Sam and Suzy, but a fierce storm is also heading their way.

programme.desc: Fanny and Jean have everything of the ideal couple: fulfilled in their professional life, they live in a magnificent apartment and seem to be in love as on the first day. But when Fanny crosses, by chance, Alain, a former high school friend, she is immediately capsized.

programme.title: The Flay List
programme.desc: Seen by many as the gastronomical capital of the world, New York is a city full of diverse cuisines and fabulous fares, revered for its sheer number of restaurants and high-quality chefs. Celebrity chef and restaurateur Bobby Flay, accompanied by his daughter Sophie, is on a mission to explore the city's heralded food scene, hoping to uncover some true local gems. Focussing on the fares that Americans love the most, from spicy tacos to Italian-style pizza, sumptuous steaks to luxurious lobster and heavenly fried chicken to scrumptious burgers, the pair hit the streets with their taste-buds salivating.

programme.title: Bobby Flay's Barbecue Addiction
programme.desc: There's nothing more satisfying than taking to the open air, armed with a trusty barbecue, and grilling up some delicious cuts of meat. In this unique series, chef Bobby Flay does exactly that, bringing the viewer along with him as he demonstrates the art of a good barbecue, complete with expert grilling techniques. Using ingredients from around the world, and with an entertaining them each episode, Bobby puts the flames to the test, delivering the perfect barbecuing experience.

programme.title: The Kitchen
programme.desc: Join chefs Sunny Anderson, Jeff Mauro, Marcela Valladolid as well as chef Katie Lee and Iron Chef Geoffrey Zakarian as they show you how to make simple and delicious meals for your friends and family, while also having lots of fun together in ''The Kitchen''. With interesting and easy recipes, incredible guests, and hilarious hosts and their amazing interaction, you will enjoy this cooking-themed talk show.

programme.title: Kids Baking Championship
programme.desc: Join the contestants as they compete for the title of 'Kids Baking Champion', and a grand prize of up to $25,000. Hosted and judged by actress Valerie Bartinelli and celebrity baker Duff Goldman, the children are tasked with a number of difficult baking challenges, serving up mouth-wateringly delicious sweet and savoury treats. With up to 12 children hoping to prove they're the best young baker in the competition, each contestant must showcase their incredible culinary skills in order to impress the judges and take home the title.

programme.title: Jenny and Reza's Fabulous Food Academy
programme.desc: Chief Jenny Morrison known as the Giggling Gourmet and her south African cousin and Chief Reza Mohammad known for his India dishes. They will be teaming up as presenter for Food network reality cooking television show called Jenny Rezas Fabulous Food Academy. The goal of the show is for the chief to teach six people how to cook the most basic dish to the inventive dish of other cultures. Using ingredients from all around the world. Come and see what these six people will be make from the celebrity chiefs.

programme.title: Chopped
programme.desc: Chopped is an American reality cooking TV game show hosted by Ted Allen. Four chefs compete against each other. At the beginning of each round they receive a basket containing four mystery ingredients and are expected to create the best three-course meal using every single one of them. Each round has a time limit. The dishes are judged based on their presentation, taste and creativity. At the end of every round one chef is "chopped" from the competition with no prize. The winner can get up to $50.000.

Ryan Murphy, Brad Falchuk and Tim Minear reimagine the procedural drama with "9-1-1." The series explores the high-pressure experiences of first responders -- including police officers, firefighters and dispatchers -- who are thrust into the most frightening, shocking and heart-stopping situations. These emergency responders must try to balance saving those who are at their most vulnerable with solving the problems in their own lives. The show draws from real-life, high-pressure experiences of first responders who regularly face heart-stopping situations that are often unpredictable, intense and uplifting at the same time.

programme.title: M.O.D.O.K.
programme.desc: Lou, feeling like M.O.D.O.K. is stifling his individuality ahead of his bar mitzvah, jumps into M.O.D.O.K.'s portal to Asgard. He refuses to go back home with his dad, so M.O.D.O.K. takes control of an army of Asgardian warriors and wages war against his son. Eventually, M.O.D.O.K. and Lou strike a deal and use Lou's magic tricks to pacify the Kobolds. Meanwhile, the Super Adaptoid agrees to help young M.O.D.O.K.

programme.title: M.O.D.O.K.
programme.desc: In a bid to save his marriage, M.O.D.O.K. takes Jodie back in time to a concert they missed when they were in college. The couple reconciles but is stuck in the past until they catch up to the present. Once in the present, they prevent themselves from ever going to the past in the first place, erasing their entire adventure from the timeline.

programme.title: M.O.D.O.K.

programme.title: Solar Opposites

programme.title: Solar Opposites

Ryan Murphy, Brad Falchuk and Tim Minear reimagine the procedural drama with "9-1-1." The series explores the high-pressure experiences of first responders -- including police officers, firefighters and dispatchers -- who are thrust into the most frightening, shocking and heart-stopping situations. These emergency responders must try to balance saving those who are at their most vulnerable with solving the problems in their own lives. The show draws from real-life, high-pressure experiences of first responders who regularly face heart-stopping situations that are often unpredictable, intense and uplifting at the same time.

And lonely schoolboy Barney doesn't have a B-Bot in this animated comedy adventure featuring the voices of Zach Galifianakis, Olivia Colman and Rob Delaney. But what is a B-Bot? It's a pill-shaped robot that becomes a child's indispensable friend, connecting them via the "Bubble" network to all the content they can consume and all the friends they could ever want. Sadly Ron's family - dad Graham (Ed Helms) and grandma Donka (Colman) - can't afford one. At least, they can't afford a new one. Fortunately - or not - they find Ron (Galifianakis) round the back of the Bubble store. Ron doesn't function so well. But he's endearing. And naughty. And Barney grows to love him just the way he is. What will the other kids make of Ron? And will Bubble stand for this outrage? Well, no because their mean CEO Andrew Morris (Delaney) just won't let it lie. Written by Peter Baynham (Arthur Christmas, Hotel Transylvania) and Sarah Smith. The latter also co-directs with Jean-Philippe Vine and Octavio E. Rodriguez.

programme.title: Hop
programme.desc: (2011) Easter-themed part-animated, part live-action children's comedy from Tim Hill (director of Alvin and the Chipmunks), featuring the voices of Russell Brand, Hugh Laurie and Hank Azaria. On Easter Island, Easter Bunny (voiced by Laurie) is the head of the family of rabbits who have control of the global Easter confectionery business. He's keen to begin to hand over the organisation to his son EB (voiced by Brand), but unfortunately EB has no interest in his family's enterprise. Instead, EB abandons the island for Hollywood to pursue his ambition of becoming a rock drummer. In the (live-action) States, the animated rabbit throws his lot in with Fred O'Hare (James Marsden), a slacker approaching 40 who still lives with his parents. Together they embark on a series of adventures, which include EB's attempt to get in to Hugh Hefner's Playboy Mansion. But trouble is brewing back on Easter Island, where Carlos (voiced by Azaria), a huge chick who oversees the confectionery distribution network, is plotting to take over the business in a coup... Network premiere.

programme.title: Hotel Transylvania 3: Summer Vacation
programme.desc: The third instalment of the spooky animated comedy sees Adam Sandler, Selena Gomez and Andy Samberg reprise their roles as a family of misfit monsters. Everyone around Dracula (Sandler) is busy getting hitched and falling in love, yet poor Drac can't seem to find his 'zing'. But when his daughter Mavis (Gomez) takes him and the family on a monster-friendly cruise, things take a sudden turn. Captain Ericka (Kathryn Hahn) is the apparently bubbly, kind-hearted woman running the ship, and it's love at first sight for our vampiric friend. There's just one problem: Ericka comes from a long line of monster hunters, and she wants Dracula dead. Talk about red flags. Luckily, Dracula is a dab hand at unwittingly avoiding murder attempts. Nothing she throws at him sticks... or, ahem, stakes. And after spending some time with the family of ghosts, ghouls and assorted wretches, Ericka begins to doubt everything she's ever known. Maybe monsters aren't so bad after all. And maybe - just maybe - there's hope for this unconventional romance. First play on Film4.

programme.title: The Mad Women's Ball
programme.desc: A woman who is unfairly institutionalized at a Paris asylum plots to escape with the help of one of its nurses. Based on the novel 'Le bal des folles' by Victoria Mas.

programme.title: The Upside
programme.desc: The Upside is director Neil Burger's heartfelt comedy about a recently paroled ex-convict (Kevin Hart) who strikes up an unlikely friendship with a paralyzed billionaire (Bryan Cranston). The film also stars Nicole Kidman, Julianna Margulies and Aja Naomi King. Phillip is a wealthy quadriplegic who needs a caretaker to help him with his day-to-day routine in his New York penthouse. He decides to hire Dell, a struggling parolee who's trying to reconnect with his ex and his young son. Despite coming from two different worlds, an unlikely friendship starts to blossom as Dell and Phillip rediscover the joy of living life to the fullest.

programme.title: All Is True
programme.desc: The year is 1613, Shakespeare (Kenneth Branagh) is acknowledged as the greatest writer of the age. But disaster strikes when his renowned Globe Theatre burns to the ground, and devastated, Shakespeare returns to Stratford, where he must face a troubled past and a neglected family. Haunted by the death of his only son Hamnet, he struggles to mend the broken relationships with his wife (Judi Dench) and daughters. In so doing, he is ruthlessly forced to examine his own failings as husband and father. His very personal search for the truth uncovers secrets and lies within a family at war.

programme.title: Spider-Man: No Way Home
programme.desc: For the first time in the cinematic history of Spider-Man, our friendly neighborhood hero's identity is revealed, bringing his Super Hero responsibilities into conflict with his normal life and putting those he cares about most at risk. When he enlists Doctor Strange's help to restore his secret, the spell tears a hole in their world, releasing the most powerful villains who've ever fought a Spider-Man in any universe. Now, Peter will have to overcome his greatest challenge yet, which will not only forever alter his own future but the future of the Multiverse.

programme.title: Basketball: EuroLeague. Crvena zvezda - AS Monaco
programme.desc: The EuroLeague is the top-tier European professional basketball club competition since 2000. The competition replaced the FIBA EuroLeague (which was previously called the FIBA European Champions Cup, or simply the European Cup), which had been run by FIBA since 1958. Starting from 2010/2011 season the tournament is named Turkish Airlines Euroleague, due to a sponsorship contract of Turkish Airlines with EuroLeague, and in 2013 the contract was prolonged to 2020. The tournament is aired in 199 countries of the world. The current EuroLeague structure is made up of 16 teams, which each play each other twice, once at home and once away, in a double round robin league regular season, each team plays 30 games. The top 8 placed teams at the end of the regular season advance to playoffs, each plays a 5 game playoff series against a single opponent. The winners of each playoff series advance to the Final Four held in a predetermined city for two days. The Final Four features two semifinals, a third place game, and the championship game, all on the same weekend.

programme.desc: In Flip to A Million, HGTV will conduct an edge-of-your-seat house-flipping experiment as never seen before. The six one-hour episodes will follow two couples who are both successful house flippers in their respective markets: Jason and EJ Williams of Chicago, Illinois, and Jon and Dani Wrobel of Long Island, New York. During the series, narrated by HGTV star Alison Victoria, the pairs will be dropped in an unfamiliar city—Dallas, Texas—where they will set out to prove that, in the world of real estate, it's possible to start out with almost nothing and turn it into a fortune. With an initial budget of only $1,000, each couple will work the real estate and flipping market to buy, renovate and sell properties. Their goal: build to a $1 million house sale in just six months. To try to make it happen, the duos must take real risks and go to any length to flip to a million.

programme.title: Flip To A Million
programme.desc: In Flip to A Million, HGTV will conduct an edge-of-your-seat house-flipping experiment as never seen before. The six one-hour episodes will follow two couples who are both successful house flippers in their respective markets: Jason and EJ Williams of Chicago, Illinois, and Jon and Dani Wrobel of Long Island, New York. During the series, narrated by HGTV star Alison Victoria, the pairs will be dropped in an unfamiliar city—Dallas, Texas—where they will set out to prove that, in the world of real estate, it's possible to start out with almost nothing and turn it into a fortune. With an initial budget of only $1,000, each couple will work the real estate and flipping market to buy, renovate and sell properties. Their goal: build to a $1 million house sale in just six months. To try to make it happen, the duos must take real risks and go to any length to flip to a million.

programme.title: Brad Meltzer's Lost History
programme.desc: Brad Meltzer and viewers are on the hunt for lost history. Among the missing: actual lunar rocks brought back from the moon by American astronauts during the Apollo space program - and later stolen from NASA headquarters in a daring heist.

programme.title: Digging for the Truth
programme.desc: An intriguing exploration of some of the most incredible ancient mysteries located all around the world. The presenter questions the existing theories on the subjects, talks to experts and gives his own hypothesis on what could have happened. Join this amazing historical journey as iconic mysteries such as the Egyptian pyramids, the Holy Grail and the Lost Ark of the Covenent are explored.

programme.title: The Universe
programme.desc: Every day, new information is discovered that helps us better understand how our Universe works. Some of this evidence solves mysteries dating back thousands of years. Some evidence offers new theories on how human civilization came into existence. In this season of The Universe: Ancient Mysteries Solved, we'll tackle mysteries such as an American Stonehenge built 500 years before Columbus, and how the Aztec Pyramids helped seal the downfall of the Mayan and Aztec empires. We'll also look at some of the Roman Empires' most iconic structures, and their connection to archeo-astronomy.

programme.title: Unidentified: Inside America's UFO Investigation
programme.desc: This documentary series features testimony from Luis Elizondo, former military intelligence official and Special Agent In-Charge at the Pentagon's mysterious program, The Advanced Aerospace Threat Identification Program (AATIP). This secretive military department was tasked with researching and investigating Unidentified Aerial Phenomena (UAP) which included numerous video clips, three of which were released to a shocked public in 2017. In this six-part series, Elizondo speaks out about his concerns for national security and the Pentagon's lack of response to these potential threats. Episodes include fighter pilots from the USS Nimitz describing their terrifying encounter with a UFO; the lights seen in the sky above a New Jersey turnpike; and a saucer-shaped craft observed over Chicago's O'Hare airport.

programme.title: Ancient Aliens
programme.desc: ANCIENT ALIENS examines 75 million years of the most credible alien evidence here on Earth, from the age of the dinosaurs, to ancient Egypt, to the skies over the western desert in the present day US. Ancient cave drawings of strange creatures, an asphalt-like substance in an Egyptian pyramid made from the remains of unidentified creatures, continued mass sightings in the USA -- these are just a few of the strange stories that will be investigated.

programme.title: Cities of the Underworld
programme.desc: In major cities around the world today, skyscrapers loom overhead, taxis honk their horns and street vendors peddle their wares. But below lies city upon city - each with its fascinating and unknown history. This series will explore these layers, which are often hundreds of feet deep, and examine a city's ancient cisterns, dank dungeons, eerie tombs, clandestine hideouts, and even underground shipwrecks that have been lost for hundreds and hundreds of years. What are the underground layers of the most populated cities on earth? And how did (and do) engineers build layer upon layer up to today's city streets? This series will reveal the technological marvels that allowed the construction of one city upon another - literally.

programme.title: Bible Secrets Revealed
programme.desc: Documentary series in which viewers have a chance to explore the mysteries and reveal secrets and hidden facts of the world's most famous and oldest book - the Bible. For thousands of years, The Holy Bible has been the foundation on which Judaism and Christianity are built, but there are still many secrets and things which can be interpreted differently. Featuring stunning on-location photography, interesting reenactments and interviews with scientists, archaeologists and religious leaders, this series will take us on remarkable journey back in time to see what the Old Testament and the New Testament are hiding from us - from Dead Sea Scrolls, examinations of the traditional belief that Moses wrote the Torah, to whether Adam and Eve were created together or one before the other, who authored the New Testament and many other mysteries.

programme.title: How the Earth Was Made
programme.desc: With the help of expert geologists and various scientists, How the Earth Was Made is a remarkable documentary series that examines the powerful forces and events that have shaped our planet. Using stunning, computer generated cinematography, viewers are transported back billions of years to learn how our planet was formed, and the drastically different changes it has witnessed. Each episode focusses on a different location to explore how it has adapted and adjusted over millions of years, such as the Grand Canyon, Mount Everest, the Sahara desert and the Mariana Trench.

programme.desc: In major cities around the world today, skyscrapers loom overhead, taxis honk their horns and street vendors peddle their wares. But below lies city upon city - each with its fascinating and unknown history. This series will explore these layers, which are often hundreds of feet deep, and examine a city's ancient cisterns, dank dungeons, eerie tombs, clandestine hideouts, and even underground shipwrecks that have been lost for hundreds and hundreds of years. What are the underground layers of the most populated cities on earth? And how did (and do) engineers build layer upon layer up to today's city streets? This series will reveal the technological marvels that allowed the construction of one city upon another - literally.

programme.title: Bible Secrets Revealed
programme.desc: Documentary series in which viewers have a chance to explore the mysteries and reveal secrets and hidden facts of the world's most famous and oldest book - the Bible. For thousands of years, The Holy Bible has been the foundation on which Judaism and Christianity are built, but there are still many secrets and things which can be interpreted differently. Featuring stunning on-location photography, interesting reenactments and interviews with scientists, archaeologists and religious leaders, this series will take us on remarkable journey back in time to see what the Old Testament and the New Testament are hiding from us - from Dead Sea Scrolls, examinations of the traditional belief that Moses wrote the Torah, to whether Adam and Eve were created together or one before the other, who authored the New Testament and many other mysteries.

programme.title: How the Earth Was Made
programme.desc: With the help of expert geologists and various scientists, How the Earth Was Made is a remarkable documentary series that examines the powerful forces and events that have shaped our planet. Using stunning, computer generated cinematography, viewers are transported back billions of years to learn how our planet was formed, and the drastically different changes it has witnessed. Each episode focusses on a different location to explore how it has adapted and adjusted over millions of years, such as the Grand Canyon, Mount Everest, the Sahara desert and the Mariana Trench.

programme.title: Food Tech
programme.desc: Nothing beats the taste of a Southern fried meal and Bobby traces its amazing journey to your plate. In Alabama, Bobby wades among 275,000 catfish during feeding time, and discovers how each fish scooped from the pond becomes a fillet within an hour.

programme.title: Serial Killer Earth
programme.desc: Gripping and unsettling documentary series that features a team of experts who in each episode examine various footage from news and home video, as well as eyewitness testimony, in order to explain, understand and inform viewers of what actually happened during some of the most devastating natural disasters- including Hurricane Katrina, the earthquake and tsunami that devastated Japan, a monstrous earthquake in Haiti, avalanche of rocks and debris that destroyed a village in Honduras, and many other hurricanes, earthquakes, tsunamis, floodings, droughts and devastating forest fires. They will also investigate how these recent disasters compare and contrast with the most historic natural disasters of the past.

programme.title: Battles BC
programme.desc: Step back in time and revisit some of the most brutal battles that took place before Christ. Recreated with stunning technology, we reveal these violent conflicts like never before, examining the soldiers, strategies and weapons deployed by the powerful legions. From Hannibal's clashes with Rome to Alexander the Great's pursuits throughout India, these conflicts have had a resounding impact on our history and with these reconstructions you will see the ferocious aspects of war in antiquity.

programme.title: Project Impossible
programme.desc: Project Impossible is an original series that follows a new generation of epic engineering projects that were considered unthinkable just a few years ago. Each episode of Project Impossible features multiple stories that illustrate man-made projects that are crucial to our future. These projects include a massive North Sea wind station with 600-foot rotors, a giant sea wall that will protect the ancient city of Venice from rising waters, the world's largest moveable structure in Chernobyl, and the construction of a fleet of nuclear powered icebreaking ships.

programme.title: Where Did It Come From?
programme.desc: Documentary series exploring the history of Earth's greatest man-made structures and creations. Where Did It Come From? reveals the earliest examples of brilliance and ingenuity from past pioneers. From the Roman highway project; a civil engineering feat establishing a network of unprecedented highways, to Egypt's iconic structures, this series reveals the incomprehensible ides brought to life by magnificent minds, and in some cases, brutal slavery. Join host Michael Guillen as he dives into this fascinating world of both civil and social engineering, born out of ideas we still use today.

programme.title: Doomsday: 10 Ways the World Will End
programme.desc: Theories of how the world will meet its end in this doomsday documentary as we follow scientist Trevor S. Valle as he hypothesises with others through the series. Looking into how the human race will be wiped out with each episode examining a different theory of how the planet will be destroyed. From being swallowed by a black hole, bombed by meteorites or overcome by aliens the series covers the most popular theories. An intriguing and interesting watch that will have you questioning how things out of this world could see the end of the earth.

programme.title: Hunting Hitler
programme.desc: An FBI cold case that has laid dormant for 70 years leads a group of world-renown investigators on the ultimate manhunt to finally answer the question: Did Adolf Hitler survive World War II? In early 2014 the FBI declassified hundreds of confidential documents showing that Hitler may have not committed suicide but rather escaped to South America after the fall of Germany. A memo from J. Edgar Hoover himself states "American Army officials in Germany have not located Hitler's body nor is there any reliable source that will say definitely that Hitler is dead." Armed with the most cutting edge technology and these newly released FBI files the team will approach this case like a modern death claims investigation. Whether they are investigating a mysterious Nazi lair deep in the Argentinian jungle or diving for evidence of a missing U-Boat that could of shuttled Hitler to South America our team will focus on the tried and tested tenants for solving a fraudulent death case: follow the money where was the subject last seen, eyewitness reports, make contact with known associates and forensics.With declassified worldwide intelligence providing a wealth of new clues and modern technology never before available we reopen this world famous cold case in hopes of solving the mystery surrounding the demise of one of the biggest criminals of all time.

programme.title: The Curse of Civil War Gold
programme.desc: The Curse of Civil War Gold is a non-fiction series about American Civil War history. Michigan native, part time treasure hunter Kevin Dykstra and his team search for lost treasures of Civil War Gold, estimated to be worth millions of dollars. They join forces with Marty Lagina from The Curse of Oak Island trying to solve the mystery and find the lost gold. The story goes that Union soldiers tracked down Confederate president Jefferson Davis in 1865 and confiscated his gold. Later it was smuggled north and ended up in Lake Michigan. And this is exactly where Kevin and his crew head to.

programme.title: Shipping Wars
programme.desc: Groups of independent shippers compete with each other in this American reality series, as they bid for the right to haul unconventional items that many conventional carriers deem unfeasible to transport. The crews must first win the right to ship the items by bidding on uShip, an online auction house that is one of the largest of its kind in the world. Once they have won the contract, they prepare the items for shipping, which is often easier said than done. The crews' performances are scrutinised throughout, and their operational abilities are pushed to their limits as they transport both bizarre and tricky shipments across the country.

programme.title: Storage Wars
programme.desc: In Storage Wars show a team of professional buyers will prove that for a good buy you need more than certain sum of money. When rent is not paid on a storage locker for a certain period, the contents can be sold as a single lot of items in the form of an auction. The best experts are fighting for containers' contents, hundreds of thousands of dollars are sometimes in the game. Every participant has only some minutes to inspect the contents, and that only without entering the storage room, just looking inside. Each purchase can become a win or a loss, and nobody knows exactly whether they are buying real treasures or garbage.

programme.title: Forged in Fire
programme.desc: Forged in Fire, an American competition series aired on the History Channel, challenges four new competitors to produce a knife in their own style with a small variety of metal objects to create from. The series, hosted by Wil Willis, consists of a three-round elimination contest to forge bladed weapons, with the final winner receiving $10,000 and the day's championship title. Judged by experts in weapon history and use, the last two people standing must create in their own forge a Moro Kris sword, a blade which dates back to 300BC, in just five days. Filmed in Brooklyn, New York, the set referred to as "The Forge" sets the scene for this suspenseful show with propane forges, power hammers and hydraulic presses, with medical personnel being close by to treat any injuries or other health problems. If the medical personnel suspect that the competitors are unable to continue safely, they will be disqualified. Once each competitor has created their weapon, it will be put through a series of tests including chopping/slashing/stabbing objects such as ropes, ice blocks, animal carcasses and steel car doors. Having to meet a number of criteria's, the smiths battle it out, without their swords, to become the best black-smith.

From old rusty bridges to ship graveyard colonized by wildlife, from military airport to Hitler's bunkers, ghost towns and abandoned villages- get to know forgotten structures that change the world.

programme.title: The Curse of Oak Island
programme.desc: The Curse of Oak Island is an active reality television series that focuses on the Oak Island mystery. There are numerous mystical stories of buried treasure and unexplained objects on or near this enigmatic island in Nova Scotia. Since the 19th century several attempts have been taken to locate treasure and artifacts there, some people even lost their lives trying to read this riddle. The Lagina brothers, Rick and Marty, were so impressed by this legend that they decided to try their luck and start this dangerous mission with the help of modern technologies and machinery. They are hammering at finding whatever is there, hidden deep under the ground, taking no notice of the fact that so far not even one research has ended up successfully.

programme.desc: Retseptimeister Rita Osale tuleb külla legendaarne saatejuht ja kalasõber Vladislav Koržets, kellega koos avardatakse toore kala söömise piire ning tehakse selgeks, miks ja millist kala üldse värskelt süüa võib. Lisaks eelroaväärilistele punase kala hõrgutistele saab värskest kohafileest valmis restoranivääriline Mannerheimi koha koos perfektselt keedetud riisi ning suus sulava mädarõikakastmega.

programme.title: Rooli võim
programme.desc: Eesti staažikaim liiklussaade, mille teemade ring ulatub automarkidest kindlustuseni. Saade paneb proovile ka tuntud inimeste sõiduoskused ning nad paljastavad, mis neid siinses liikluses häirib ning mida tuleks liikluses ümber korraldada. Muu hulgas osalevad saate tegijad ka liiklusreididel. Rooli Võim ei ole mõeldud üksnes tänastele autoomanikele ja juhtidele, vaid kõigile, kel tuleb rohkemal või vähemal määral liiklusega kokku puutuda, ehk siis ka jalakäijatele ja ühistranspordiga liiklejatele.

programme.title: Liikleja
programme.desc: Mis on Eesti liikluses valesti? Mille üle saab uhke olla? Milliste reeglite vastu kõige enam eksitakse? Saatesari "Liikleja" võtab kord kuus luubi alla ühe liiklusohutusalase teema. "Liikleja" näitab, mis toimub Eesti liikluses, annab nõu ja jagab näpunäiteid, mis on elupäästvad ning muudavad liikluse Eestis ohutumaks. Eesti riigiteedel registreeritakse aastas ligikaudu 6000 liiklusõnnetust metsloomadega! Nendes õnnetustes saab vigastada ca 20-30 inimest. Tänases "Liikleja" saates uurimegi, mida teha, kui õnnetus on juhtunud ja kuidas ennekõike selliseid kokkupõrkeid vältida! Saates saavad sõna loomade käitumise asjatundja, Eesti Jahimeeste Seltsi esindaja, Transpordiameti eksperdid ja Kindlustusseltside Liidu juht! Saatejuht on Jaanus Koort.

programme.title: Saateapsud 2024
programme.desc: Läbi aegade on rahvale pakkunud lusti vaadata teletegijate apse - nemad ka ju ikkagi inimesed! Lõbusas erisaates näeme, mis toimub tegelikult menusaadete kaadri taga ja kuidas armastatud eetrinäod ootamatute olukordadega toime tulevad! Saates näeb milliste ootamatustega on rinda pistnud "Õhtu" saatejuhtid Piret, Jüri ja Robert, mis ajab pisarateni naerma "Papside" sarja näitlejaid, mis viperused leidsid aset "Olümpiastuudios" või mille lõbusaga on saatejuht Andrei Zevakin "Noore meistri" salvestustel hakkama saanud.

programme.title: Mitme näoga Eesti
programme.desc: Sukeldume Mehhiko traditsioonidesse, et tähistada riigi üht tähtsaimat püha - Día de los Muertost ehk surnutepäeva. Kuidas erineb Eesti hingedepäev Mehhiko omast ning kas Iraanis üldse sellist päeva tähistatakse, vaata juba saatest!

programme.title: Mida toob aasta 2025?
programme.desc: Edda Pauksoni ekslusiivne aasta horoskoop ütleb, kes leiab järgmisel aastal armastuse, kes hakkab uut kodu ostma ja kes võiks mängida loteriid? Kaardimooride Kirsti Timmeri ja Ruth Pukmani põrutavad ennustused näevad nälga ja mässu. Tulemas on suur maksutõusu aasta. Kes jaksab seda maksukoormust kanda, kes kukub pikali, räägivad majanduseksperdid Raivo Vare ja Lenno Uusküla. Saatejuht on Eda-Liis Kann.

programme.title: Ma näen su häält
programme.desc: Suurejoonelises telesõus esitletakse taaskord seitsmest salapärasest lauljast koosnevat gruppi, keda identifitseeritakse nende elukutse või hobi järgi. Kaks võistlejat peavad püüdma grupist kõrvaldada halvad vokalistid ehk teesklejad. Abiks on vihjed ja kuulsustest koosnev nõunike kogu, kuhu seekord kuuluvad Evelin Võigemast, Grete Kuld, Mart Juur ning Estoni Kohver. Lisaks võtab täna nõunikepaneelis koha sisse armastatud lauljatar Eda-Ines Etti, kes saate lõpus peab viimase tundmatuga duetti laulma. Suurt meelelahutussõud juhib alati särav ja positiivne Piret Laos.

programme.title: Kodu mägedes
programme.desc: Marie saab teada Martha haigusest ja võtab üle nii tema eest hoolitsemise kui talu juhtimise. Samuti püüab ta lepitada Marthat ja ta poega. Georg näitab oma isalikke oskusi. Pärimistüli kogub tuure.

programme.title: Reporter+
programme.desc: Uudistemagasinide lipulaev, mis toob olulisemad ja põnevamad uudised kodumaalt ja mujalt maailmast vaatajateni Reporterile omasel mahlakal moel. Saatejuhid on alati soliidsed Jaanus Koort, Simon Suviste ja Tõnis Sarap.

programme.title: Kuldne pilet
programme.desc: Saatejuht Keili Sükijaineni elamuslik rännak luksuse maailma jätkub. Seekord St.Moritz - luksuskuurort, luksuskinnisvara, luksuspoed, luksus-luksus, luksus... Kuidas sai ühest väikesest Šveitsi külast koht, mis kubiseb rikkuritest? Maitseme järele, kuidas need rahakad veedavad oma päeva ühes maailma kalleimas suusakuurordis. Lisaks maitseme ka kooke, mis on kogu Instagrami hulluks ajanud. Kas 10 miljoni jälgijaga Cedric Grolet' küpsetised on tõesti nii erilised, et nende nimel tasub kümnete inimestega üheskoos Pariisi tänaval järjekorras külmetada?

programme.title: Uus algus
programme.desc: Mait on Pireti peale solvunud ja otsustab minna vabatahtlikult haiglasse tagasi, et taastuda. Õde on meelitatud ja pole raske aimata, et talle väga meeldib Maidu eest hoolitseda. Mari otsustab kodust põgeneda ning emotsioonidest läheb kaasa sõbranna rumala plaaniga teeselda röövi. Nõutakse lunaraha ning mesinädalad lükkuvad üha edasi.

programme.title: Mõrvad Männikülas
programme.desc: Gamache tähistab Manoir Belleforet' hotellis oma pulma-aastapäeva, kuid kui leitakse surnukeha, saab tema tähtpäev kiire lõpu ning ta asub oma tiimiga hotelliomanikest düsfunktsionaalset Morrow' perekonda uurima.

programme.title: Mõrvad Männikülas
programme.desc: Gamache on kindel, et on Julia mõrva lahendamisele väga lähedal. Kevinil ja Lacoste'il on omavaheline hõõrdumine ning Lacoste püüab end mõrva eest süüdi lavastamise eest kaitsta.

programme.title: Heeringas Veenuse õlal
programme.desc: Vaimukad sketšid toovad meieni armastatud Eesti näitlejad. Osades Taavi Teplenkov, Tiit Sukk, Marilyn Jurman, Tiina Tauraite, Margus Prangel ja Liina Vahtrik.

programme.title: Kuninga kõne
programme.desc: 12 Oscarile nomineeritud ajaloodraama! Lugu mehest (Colin Firth), kellest sai kuningas George VI, kuninganna Elizabeth II isa. Pärast seda, kui tema vend Edward (Guy Pearce) troonist loobub, tõuseb George, hüüdnimega Bertie, vastu tahtmist Ühendatud kuningriigi etteotsa. Bertie, kes kannatab kogelemise all ning keda ei peeta sugugi vääriliseks kuningaks, saab abi Lionel Logue'ilt (Geoffrey Rush), ebatavaliste võtetega kõneterapeudilt. Ootamatute kõnetehnikate ja ebatõenäolise sõpruse abil leiab Bertie kindla hääle ning viib riigi söakalt sõtta. Film ei sobi alaealistele.

programme.title: Jõulud jooksus
programme.desc: Romantilises jõulufilmis on Becca sunnitud ühendama jõud oma endise poiss-sõbraga, et otsida jõuluõhtul jooksu pannud koera. Kutsikas viib neid terveks ööpäevaks otsingule läbi nende Põhja-Carolina kodulinna. Selle käigus külastavad nad inimesi ja kohti, mis meenutavad neile koos veedetud jõule. Jõuluhommikuks on neil koer leitud ja armastus teineteise vastu taastunud.

programme.title: Балтия
programme.desc: "Балтия" - программа на русском языке о Балтии, о людях, которые живут в Латвии, Литве и Эстонии, говорят на разных языках, но об одном и том же. О том, что нас волнует, огорчает или радует. Мы не делим жизнь на политику и вне политики. Мы просто говорим о самом важном.

programme.title: Тихий Дон
programme.desc: Григорий работает у сотника Евгения Листницкого кучером, Аксинью берут в имение сотника кухаркой для дворовых и сезонных рабочих. Листницкий начинает проявлять к Аксинье интерес. Наталья вновь приходит жить к Мелеховым. Она по-прежнему надеется на возвращение Григория в семью. Аксинья признается Григорию, что ждет от него ребенка. Григорий уезжает на четырехгодичную службу; по дороге отец сообщает ему, что Наталья выжила, и спрашивает, будет ли Григорий жить с ней, когда вернется.

programme.title: Балтия
programme.desc: Информационная программа "Балтия" - непредвзятый взгляд на происходящее в Эстонии, Латвии и Литве. События, явления и люди в репортажах корреспондентов "Настоящего Времени", работающих в регионе. Точная и беспристрастная информация, все точки зрения о происходящем в каждой из трех стран, входящих в Евросоюз и военный блок НАТО.

programme.title: Ремонт на сдачу
programme.desc: Кейли и Мерлин направляются в Пярну на помощь Сильверу, который собирается сделать сюрприз своему отцу - преобразить его квартиру под сдачу. Всего за 2 недели им предстоит превратить тесное жилье с устаревшим интерьером в романтичное гнездышко.

programme.title: Ольга
programme.desc: Главная героиня воспитывает двух детей от разных браков, заботится об отце-алкоголике и пытается наладить личную жизнь. Старшая дочь Анька учится в ПТУ, думает, что она единственный адекватный член семьи и в её жизни все будет по-другому, младший сын Тимофей, чей отец вернулся к первой семье в Азербайджан, считает, что он уже мужчина, хотя ему всего лишь 11 лет, отец Ольги, бывший футболист, крепко выпивает и постоянно врет, а сестра Ленка пытается жить за счет мужчин, в основном — женатых. Вечно спасая родственников от неприятностей, Ольга живет чужой жизнью и редко думает о себе — до тех пор, пока в нее не влюбляется молодой и положительный водитель газели "Ритуал" Гриша.

programme.desc: Главная героиня воспитывает двух детей от разных браков, заботится об отце-алкоголике и пытается наладить личную жизнь. Старшая дочь Анька учится в ПТУ, думает, что она единственный адекватный член семьи и в её жизни все будет по-другому, младший сын Тимофей, чей отец вернулся к первой семье в Азербайджан, считает, что он уже мужчина, хотя ему всего лишь 11 лет, отец Ольги, бывший футболист, крепко выпивает и постоянно врет, а сестра Ленка пытается жить за счет мужчин, в основном — женатых. Вечно спасая родственников от неприятностей, Ольга живет чужой жизнью и редко думает о себе — до тех пор, пока в нее не влюбляется молодой и положительный водитель газели "Ритуал" Гриша.

programme.title: Панянка-селянка
programme.desc: По замыслу организаторов шоу в каждом выпуске примут участие 2 девушки: одна холеная и не бедная горожанка, а вторая - простая деревенская девчонка. Одна из них имеет спокойную работу в теплом уютном офисе, зарабатывает неплохие деньги, постоянно следит за своей внешностью и имиджем, все выходные проводит занимаясь шоппингом в крупных торгово-развлекательных центрах или развлекается с подругами в суши-барах, боулинг-клубах или кинотеатрах. Вторая участница - ведет полностью противоположный образ жизни: кормит домашнюю скотину, помогает родителям в огороде, одевается проще некуда, а зарабатывает, в лучшем случае, 1000 грн в сельском гастрономе. И вот такие две абсолютно непохожие девушки из разных миров на целых три дня поменяются местами и жизнями! Именно это и есть цель нового шоу Панянка-Селянка.

programme.title: Полёты во сне и наяву
programme.desc: Накануне своего сорокалетия герой фильма пытается подвести итоги прожитых лет. Увы: он подводит их, а они подводят его. Ничто не приносит ему удовлетворения и счастья: ни любящая жена, ни юная любовница, ни друзья, ни работа...

programme.title: Привычка расставаться
programme.desc: Привычка расставаться 18+ Романтическая комедия. 2013. Россия. Режиссёр: Екатерина Телегина В ролях: Алёна Константинова, Данила Козловский, Елизавета Боярская и др. Романтическая комедия о девушке, которая ищет настоящую любовь Случайно заметив в аэропорту молодую девушку, которая горько плакала, Ева решила рассказать ей историю своей жизни: как она влюблялась в парней, встречалась, расставалась и искала своего принца. А главное - чем закончились её поиски.

programme.title: Страна глухих
programme.desc: Рита вынуждена скрываться: её друг Алёша исчез, проиграв в рулетку чужие деньги. Её спасает и прячет у себя глухая танцовщица ночного клуба Яя, живущая единственной мечтой - накопить денег и уехать в некую сказочную \"страну глухих\", где живут только глухие люди, и поэтому царит добро и справедливость. Неожиданно девушки оказываются в центре жестокого столкновения двух кланов мафии, глухих и слышащих.

programme.title: Ловушка
programme.desc: Главе самого мощного городского мафиозного клана удалось прекратить криминальные войны. Казалось бы, он наконец-то может уйти на покой, передав дела своим молодым и дерзким помощникам. Но те слишком рьяно берутся за дело: быстро удваивают доходы, но своими жесткими методами вызывают волну всеобщего недовольства. Мечта крестного отца о тихой жизни никак не осуществится - ему постоянно приходится вмешиваться, чтобы сохранить мир. Однако о мире приходится забыть, когда после 12-ти лет тюрьмы в город возвращается крупный криминальный авторитет, готовый любой ценой вернуть утраченные позиции.

programme.title: Балтия
programme.desc: "Балтия" - программа на русском языке о Балтии, о людях, которые живут в Латвии, Литве и Эстонии, говорят на разных языках, но об одном и том же. О том, что нас волнует, огорчает или радует. Мы не делим жизнь на политику и вне политики. Мы просто говорим о самом важном.

programme.title: Тихий Дон
programme.desc: Мелеховы получают известие о гибели Григория, а через двенадцать дней из письма Петра выясняется, что Григорий жив, к тому же награжден Георгиевским крестом за спасение раненого офицера и произведен в младшие урядники. Наталья решает идти в Ягодное, упрашивать Аксинью вернуть мужа. Таня, дочь Григория и Аксиньи, заболевает скарлатиной и вскоре умирает. Аксинья сходится с приехавшим в отпуск по ранению Листницким.

programme.title: Тихий Дон
programme.desc: После госпиталя Григорий едет в Ягодное. От конюха деда Сашки он узнает о связи Аксиньи с Листницким. Григорий избивает сотника кнутом и, бросив Аксинью, возвращается в семью, к Наталье. Осенью Наталья рожает двойню. До Петра доходят слухи о неверности Дарьи, сожительствовавшей со Степаном Астаховым. Пантелей Прокофьевич принимает меры, чтобы приструнить невестку, однако это ни к чему хорошему не приводит.

programme.title: Балтия
programme.desc: Информационная программа "Балтия" - непредвзятый взгляд на происходящее в Эстонии, Латвии и Литве. События, явления и люди в репортажах корреспондентов "Настоящего Времени", работающих в регионе. Точная и беспристрастная информация, все точки зрения о происходящем в каждой из трех стран, входящих в Евросоюз и военный блок НАТО.

programme.title: Переживу
programme.desc: Актриса, режиссер и певица Света Бень даже после переезда в Берлин остается лицом белорусской независимой музыки. Благодаря совместному с Галей Чикис альбому \"Прием!\" это лицо можно видеть по всей Европе. Иногда Свете даже не хватает времени на мороженое в любимой кафешке района Нойкёльн.

programme.title: TVNET на русском
programme.desc: Гостем передачи "Кто вам платит?" в студии RUS TVNET стал журналист LTV Эвалд Дукуль, с которым мы поговорили о русском языке, расколе общества и стереотипах о Даугавпилсе.

programme.title: Ольга
programme.desc: Главная героиня воспитывает двух детей от разных браков, заботится об отце-алкоголике и пытается наладить личную жизнь. Старшая дочь Анька учится в ПТУ, думает, что она единственный адекватный член семьи и в её жизни все будет по-другому, младший сын Тимофей, чей отец вернулся к первой семье в Азербайджан, считает, что он уже мужчина, хотя ему всего лишь 11 лет, отец Ольги, бывший футболист, крепко выпивает и постоянно врет, а сестра Ленка пытается жить за счет мужчин, в основном — женатых. programme.desc: Главе самого мощного городского мафиозного клана удалось прекратить криминальные войны. Казалось бы, он наконец-то может уйти на покой, передав дела своим молодым и дерзким помощникам. programme.title: Hoodie
programme.desc: Hoodie is a superhero story about a perfectly normal boy, with an exceptional talent for parkour and a passion for justice. For two years now, he has been practising parkour with Soufian, the best tracer in Brussels. In secret, as his mother, a passionate police officer, would never approve it. When three neighbourhood kids, Flo, Basim and Kenza, discover Pieter's talent and motivation, they join him to become an unexpected superhero crew: Team Hoodie. They are connected by one goal: to liberate the neighbourhood from injustice.

programme.title: Bunk'd
programme.desc: Bunk'd shows Ravi Ross and his sisters Emma and Zuri who decide to leave noisy streets of New York and set off to a rustic summer camp Kikiwaka in Maine where their parents met as teenagers. The camp got its name after a magic creature Kikiwaka that leaves nearby. From the first minutes of their stay guys realize that holidays are not going to be easy and relaxing, as the head of Kikiwaka turns out to remember their Mom who stole her boyfriend. That boyfriend later became the father of the three. Plus the conditions in the camp are very specific and far from perfect, health code and safety regulations are seriously violated. Ravi has a weird roommate, Zuri's roommate is a nerd, so kids start to doubt whether it is worth staying. Also modern technologies like phones and notebooks are not available in the camp, which makes it even harder. Fortunately the teens are smart enough to figure out their way out of the most difficult and strange situations.

programme.title: K.C. Undercover
programme.desc: Fascinating spy series K.C. Undercover shows intriguing story of K.C. Cooper, a high school student. Just like other teenagers K.C. goes to school, does homework and wonders about her future. Her life changes drastically after she finds out that her parents are professional secret agents. K.C. wants to follow their steps and after getting their approval gets her first serious task. The main character shows both sides of her life- regular life with troubles at home and secret missions, aimed at country's rescue, sometimes rescue of the whole humankind.

programme.title: Ninjago: Dragons Rising
programme.desc: Computer-animated epic fantasy superhero sequel series. It's dragons versus Photac beasts in the streets of Imperium, but the Claws stop Lloyd and Wyldfyre's efforts to free the escaped dragons as Sora and Arin search for Riyu. The young dragon's spark would allow Sora to shut down the Photacs for good - unfortunately, the Teen Protection Force brings him before the Empress... Meanwhile, Nya and Kai reunite under mysterious circumstances and face an apparition.

programme.title: Horrid Henry
programme.desc: Horrid Henry is always getting in trouble. He is a head strong, prankster with a strong disregard for authority. His selfish ways cause chaos wherever he goes, and he is relentless when it comes to outsmarting enemies, teachers, babysitters, or pretty much any adult. And to make matters worse Henry's little brother Peter is Perfect. Whilst Henry never seems to learn from his Horrid behvaiour, Perfect Peter's gets more perfect every day.

programme.title: Ghostwriter
programme.desc: When a ghost haunts a neighborhood bookstore and starts releasing fictional characters into the real world, a group of friends work to solve an exciting mystery surrounding the ghost's unfinished business. The Emmy Award-winning series, which has also earned a highly coveted Prix Jeunesse Award, a Parents' Choice Gold Medal Award and recognition from Common Sense Media since its debut, was developed for television by J.J. Johnson and Andrew Orenstein with Academy Award-winning and DGA Award-nominated Luke Matheny directing five episodes from the season. Matheny and Orenstein executive produce alongside Johnson, Christin Simms, and Blair Powers for Sinking Ship Entertainment and Kay Wilson Stallings for Sesame Workshop.

programme.title: Power Rangers Dino Charge
programme.desc: In this children's series, based on a prehistoric Earth where an alien entrusted powerful Energems to 10 dinosaurs, but when the dinosaurs went extinct, the Energems were lost. Now an intergalactic bounty hunter is determined to reclaim the Energems and destroy our planet. A new team of Power Rangers must find the lost Energems and use their Dino Chargers to power up a dino-fueled battle gear, Zords and Megazords to save the world. Will the Power Rangers be able to save our planet?

programme.title: Lego Friends: The Next Chapter

programme.title: Polly Pocket
programme.desc: Often told she is too little to do all the things she wants to do, Polly doesn't let this stand in her way and proves what every kid should know... that being little isn't a limitation. Inheriting a magic locket that allows her to shrink to only 4 inches tall, she discovers that no matter how small she is, she can still have big adventures and create a big difference for her and her best friends! programme.title: Boy Girl Dog Cat Mouse Cheese
programme.desc: When Cheese accidentally begins writing her new fantasy novel inside Boy's diary, Boy is inspired to live out the life of the novel's great hero! By applying the story to his life Boy is soon one of the cool kids, and it drives Girl nuts. When she sees Cheese's novel-writing is the cause, Girl helps her write the next chapter to take Boy down a few pegs! But in doing so, it sets Boy up to get a huge beating from the biggest kid in his crew!

programme.title: Sisters
programme.desc: Comedy animation about two close siblings, both with big characters, who are at the same time both best friends and each other's biggest enemy. Wendy is a 13-year-old girl who likes to listen to music, use her phone and hang out with her boyfriend. Wendy is eager to be grown up and mature. But her energetic little sister, Marine, is often close by with a headful of crazy ideas. Wendy is irritated by Marine and the invasion of her privacy. But although they can fight, as sisters do, they are very loyal to each other and always make up in the end.

programme.title: Hoodie
programme.desc: Hoodie is a superhero story about a perfectly normal boy, with an exceptional talent for parkour and a passion for justice. For two years now, he has been practising parkour with Soufian, the best tracer in Brussels. In secret, as his mother, a passionate police officer, would never approve it. They are connected by one goal: to liberate the neighbourhood from injustice.

programme.title: K.C. Undercover

K.C. wants to follow their steps and after getting their approval gets her first serious task. The main character shows both sides of her life- regular life with troubles at home and secret missions, aimed at country's rescue, sometimes rescue of the whole humankind.

programme.title: Bunk'd
programme.desc: Bunk'd shows Ravi Ross and his sisters Emma and Zuri who decide to leave noisy streets of New York and set off to a rustic summer camp Kikiwaka in Maine where their parents met as teenagers. The camp got its name after a magic creature Kikiwaka that leaves nearby. From the first minutes of their stay guys realize that holidays are not going to be easy and relaxing, as the head of Kikiwaka turns out to remember their Mom who stole her boyfriend. That boyfriend later became the father of the three. Plus the conditions in the camp are very specific and far from perfect, health code and safety regulations are seriously violated. Ravi has a weird roommate, Zuri's roommate is a nerd, so kids start to doubt whether it is worth staying. Also modern technologies like phones and notebooks are not available in the camp, which makes it even harder. Fortunately the teens are smart enough to figure out their way out of the most difficult and strange situations.

Dennis the Menace wreaks havoc and mayhem wherever he goes. Along with his trusty sidekick, an Abyssinian wire-haired tripe hound called Gnasher and their pals Rubi, JJ, Pieface they cause all kinds of disruption in the streets of Beanotown. Dennis and his friends have plenty of tricks, pranks and crazy schemes up their sleeves and do not let the rules get of the way of them having fun.

programme.title: Boy Girl Dog Cat Mouse Cheese
programme.desc: Boy's siblings get jealous when Boy begins baking amazing cookies that he shares ONLY with his new pen pal Gretchen. So the five band together and pretend to be Gretchen, writing letters to Boy and asking him to send more cookies, which they then intercept and eat for themselves. But when Boy asks to meet Gretchen in person, Girl, Dog, Cat, Mouse and Cheese come up with a crazy plan to actually become a FAKE Gretchen so that they can steal Boy's cookie recipe once and for all!

programme.title: Boy Girl Dog Cat Mouse Cheese
programme.desc: When Cheese accidentally begins writing her new fantasy novel inside Boy's diary, Boy is inspired to live out the life of the novel's great hero! By applying the story to his life Boy is soon one of the cool kids, and it drives Girl nuts. When she sees Cheese's novel-writing is the cause, Girl helps her write the next chapter to take Boy down a few pegs! But in doing so, it sets Boy up to get a huge beating from the biggest kid in his crew!

programme.title: Sisters
programme.desc: Comedy animation about two close siblings, both with big characters, who are at the same time both best friends and each other's biggest enemy. Wendy is a 13-year-old girl who likes to listen to music, use her phone and hang out with her boyfriend. Wendy is eager to be grown up and mature. But her energetic little sister, Marine, is often close by with a headful of crazy ideas. Wendy is irritated by Marine and the invasion of her privacy. But although they can fight, as sisters do, they are very loyal to each other and always make up in the end.

programme.title: Hoodie
programme.desc: Hoodie is a superhero story about a perfectly normal boy, with an exceptional talent for parkour and a passion for justice. For two years now, he has been practising parkour with Soufian, the best tracer in Brussels. In secret, as his mother, a passionate police officer, would never approve it. When three neighbourhood kids, Flo, Basim and Kenza, discover Pieter's talent and motivation, they join him to become an unexpected superhero crew: Team Hoodie. They are connected by one goal: to liberate the neighbourhood from injustice.

programme.title: K.C. Undercover
programme.desc: Fascinating spy series K.C. Undercover shows intriguing story of K.C. Cooper, a high school student. Just like other teenagers K.C. goes to school, does homework and wonders about her future. Her life changes drastically after she finds out that her parents are professional secret agents. K.C. wants to follow their steps and after getting their approval gets her first serious task. The main character shows both sides of her life- regular life with troubles at home and secret missions, aimed at country's rescue, sometimes rescue of the whole humankind.

programme.title: Bunk'd
programme.desc: Bunk'd shows Ravi Ross and his sisters Emma and Zuri who decide to leave noisy streets of New York and set off to a rustic summer camp Kikiwaka in Maine where their parents met as teenagers. The camp got its name after a magic creature Kikiwaka that leaves nearby. From the first minutes of their stay guys realize that holidays are not going to be easy and relaxing, as the head of Kikiwaka turns out to remember their Mom who stole her boyfriend. That boyfriend later became the father of the three. Plus the conditions in the camp are very specific and far from perfect, health code and safety regulations are seriously violated. Ravi has a weird roommate, Zuri's roommate is a nerd, so kids start to doubt whether it is worth staying. Also modern technologies like phones and notebooks are not available in the camp, which makes it even harder. Fortunately the teens are smart enough to figure out their way out of the most difficult and strange situations.

programme.title: Ghostwriter
programme.desc: When a ghost haunts a neighborhood bookstore and starts releasing fictional characters into the real world, a group of friends work to solve an exciting mystery surrounding the ghost's unfinished business. The Emmy Award-winning series, which has also earned a highly coveted Prix Jeunesse Award, a Parents' Choice Gold Medal Award and recognition from Common Sense Media since its debut, was developed for television by J.J. Johnson and Andrew Orenstein with Academy Award-winning and DGA Award-nominated Luke Matheny directing five episodes from the season. Matheny and Orenstein executive produce alongside Johnson, Christin Simms, and Blair Powers for Sinking Ship Entertainment and Kay Wilson Stallings for Sesame Workshop.

The charming and humorous stories reveal the importance and power of having meaningful friendships. Among many of the subjects covered, episodes touch on issues such as trust, helping others, overcoming difficulties, curiosity, bravery, and being creative.

programme.title: Bluey
programme.desc: Bluey is Australian TV animated series, the main character is a Blue Heeler puppy named Bluey, he lives with his family: father Bandit, mother Chilli and his younger sister Bingo. It is worthy of note that Blue Heeler is an Australian breed that is in top ten according to intelligence level. Bluey is a tireless, smart, quick puppy, extremely curious in everything that is going on around him. Bingo is always by his side in his adventures. Bluey's family relationship is very warm, supportive and realistic, that arouses additional interest in this series. This kind of family reminds us of our own families or of the ones we want to have. Each story is an emotional true event from everyday real life with its own drama, lessons and conclusions.

Peppa likes to jump in muddy puddles and play with her best friend Suzy Ship. George is too small, he barely talks, he never separates from his toy dinosaur. Mummy Pig and Daddy Pig are loving and caring parents, they go to work every day. Whether they're playing games, going to the playground or visiting their cousins, Peppa and her family are there to educate on everything life-related.

programme.title: The Miniwhats
programme.desc: The MiniWhats are a joyful gang of six friends. Like most kids, they use drawings to find answers to their daily life questions… To do so, they use a magic pencil, bringing all their sketches to life. What a lucky bunch!

programme.title: Paprika
programme.desc: The Paprika Twins Stan and Olivia live on an imaginative island and are always looking to make their day more exciting. The energetic duo never let anything get in their way, not even Stan's wheelchair. Supported by their friends Big foot, Puff, Podium and Magma the Paprika twins can turn any boring day into a wild adventure, making friends and singing songs along the way. Stan has a disability and can be recognised by his wheelchair doubles, which allow Olivia to tag along without having to run alongside him meaning they can always stick together. The almost identical twins couldn't be more different, However their differences is exactly why they're such a perfectly balanced duo.

programme.title: Teletubbies
programme.desc: Teletubbies stars iconic characters; Tinky Winky, Dipsy, Laa-Laa and Po. Their world is full of love and laughter as they explore Home Dome and the magical countryside of Teletubbyland through play. Familiar and beloved features from the original series return - The Noo-noo, Tubby Custard, Tubby Toast, Baby Sun, rabbits and the Voice Trumpets - along with some brand new surprises. Look out for the Tubby Phone and the Teletubbies' touch screen tummies which link to preschool children exploring, laughing and learning - just like the Teletubbies!

programme.title: Thomas & Friends
programme.desc: Thomas and Friends presents life on Island of Sodor somewhere in Britain. There are several railways where all machines are animate creatures, they live and work there. Each of them tries to perform their job perfectly. The main character is a little blue tank engine Thomas, who travels to different places, gets to know different people and helps everybody who need it. Sometimes Thomas makes mistakes but it only teaches him not to repeat them in future. His friends are as hardworking as he is. Thomas and his team deliver mails, repair railway, take passengers wherever they need. Thomas and Friends can teach young viewers significant lessons of true value of friendship and importance of teamwork.

programme.title: Pikwik Pack
programme.desc: Pikwik Pack follows four adorable animals, Suki the hedgehog, Axel the raccoon, Tibor the hippo and Hazel the cat as they deliver magical packages filled with love to the kind citizens of Pikwik. Every day, a new surprise package arrives. The team might face rough rapids, stormy skies, or a foggy forest, but when they work together, they always deliver! The series is packed with big adventures, silly hijinks, and heartfelt charm that will entertain preschoolers while underscoring the value of community, responsibility and teamwork.

programme.title: Bluey
programme.desc: Bluey is Australian TV animated series, the main character is a Blue Heeler puppy named Bluey, he lives with his family: father Bandit, mother Chilli and his younger sister Bingo. It is worthy of note that Blue Heeler is an Australian breed that is in top ten according to intelligence level. Bluey is a tireless, smart, quick puppy, extremely curious in everything that is going on around him. Bingo is always by his side in his adventures. Bluey's family relationship is very warm, supportive and realistic, that arouses additional interest in this series. This kind of family reminds us of our own families or of the ones we want to have. Each story is an emotional true event from everyday real life with its own drama, lessons and conclusions.

Jett's going to need a SUPERCHARGE to get a pumpkin-headed Donnie under control, and he's going to need a new Super Wing to assist - the boy in his Super Wings costume!

programme.title: The Adventures of Little Penguin
programme.desc: Oscar and Leah hang out with Charles, even though he is annoyed by the crabs, who keep them company and interfere with all their knitting. Ari, the flying Hamster, suddenly arrives, and everyone is dazzled by his pilot smarts. Charles, not so much. Ari is called away on a rescue mission, and Charles also wants to impress - with his new bubble-making machine. Oscar, Leah, and Charles can fly within each of their bubbles. Until times run out. The bubbles pop, and all three fall to the ground: Oscar and Leah are saved by the returning Ari, and Charles is protected by - a safety net knitted by the crabs!

programme.title: The Adventures of Little Penguin
programme.desc: Life is good on the beach. But who lurches in the bushes? Emile. He manages to sneak in a fake treasure map in the book of Sinoe. Oscar, Leah, and Charles set out to explore the map. Many elaborate attacks from Emile fail spectacularly along the way, and our three friends don't even notice. As they reach the goal of the fake treasure map - a real treasure awaits! A galleon full of gold coins. Emile's last attempt to reverse his bad luck is also a fiasco, and the great galleon, held up by balloons, drifts into a beautiful sunset with our three friends on board - and Emile dangling from a rope. And they still didn't notice him!

programme.desc: Visit the enchanted kingdom located in a tree in our hero, Tom's, backyard. Tom is blessed with the magic movement power of "tree fu" which transforms him into a "treeling" and he is transported to Treetopolis. There, along with his friends Twigs, Arilea and Zigzoo, he revels in adventures and mishaps often involving the troublesome Mushas who enjoy causing chaos for their neighbours. Tom usually has to rely on the help of the viewer to save the day as they perform their own "tree fu" moves and transfer the magic through the screen. As well as providing social development benefits to children, the show specifically encourages the kids to partake in therapeutic movements involving sweeping arms, stomping feet, and the clenching and relaxing of fists which keep kids engaged and physically active.

Stan has a disability and can be recognised by his wheelchair doubles, which allow Olivia to tag along without having to run alongside him meaning they can always stick together. programme.title: The Miniwhats
programme.desc: The MiniWhats are a joyful gang of six friends. Like most kids, they use drawings to find answers to their daily life questions… To do so, they use a magic pencil, bringing all their sketches to life. What a lucky bunch!

programme.title: The Adventures of Little Penguin
programme.desc: Oscar and Leah continue their quest alone. They are in the jungle now and soon find themselves surrounded and captured by angry worms. In an underground cave, the worms are holding our friends captured, together with a voodoo penguin, Ernest. With a giant laser cannon, the worms turn all three penguins into - other worms. And they let loose a giant, scary cuckoo who loves to eat worms. The ensuing fight is dramatic, but even as worms, Oscar and Leah supplement each other in excellent teamwork, and finally, the good order of things is restored. But from now on, the worms make sure to feed the cuckoo very well.

programme.title: The Adventures of Little Penguin
programme.desc: Oscar Leah and Ernest, the voodoo penguin, walk through the wondrous nature when they reach the famous Three of Life, depicted in the Book of Sinoe. Ernest is reunited with his crowd, but something is off: Emile and a couple of mean sheep now run the place! Oscar is put to rough game challenges, and it all culminates with a spectacular showdown between Oscar, Leah, and Ernest on one team and Emile and two sheep on the other, on the grand ball pitch. Teamwork and aiding each other will win the day.

programme.title: Thomas & Friends
programme.desc: Thomas and Friends presents life on Island of Sodor somewhere in Britain. There are several railways where all machines are animate creatures, they live and work there. Each of them tries to perform their job perfectly. The main character is a little blue tank engine Thomas, who travels to different places, gets to know different people and helps everybody who need it. Sometimes Thomas makes mistakes but it only teaches him not to repeat them in future. His friends are as hardworking as he is. Thomas and his team deliver mails, repair railway, take passengers wherever they need. Thomas and Friends can teach young viewers significant lessons of true value of friendship and importance of teamwork.

programme.title: Pikwik Pack
programme.desc: Pikwik Pack follows four adorable animals, Suki the hedgehog, Axel the raccoon, Tibor the hippo and Hazel the cat as they deliver magical packages filled with love to the kind citizens of Pikwik. Every day, a new surprise package arrives. The team might face rough rapids, stormy skies, or a foggy forest, but when they work together, they always deliver! The series is packed with big adventures, silly hijinks, and heartfelt charm that will entertain preschoolers while underscoring the value of community, responsibility and teamwork.

programme.title: Heidi
programme.desc: Heidi is a little girl who is full of beans. She faces many problems up in the Swiss alps whilst living with her grandfather. Heidi lights up and soothes the people and animals all around her, with her enthusiastic, generous and wonderful zest for life. This bubbly, young orphan girl will learn the priceless value of friendship and mutual respect. Follow her journey as she discovers life's ups and downs.

programme.title: Ready Jet Go!
programme.desc: Sean, who has an all-consuming drive for science facts, and Sydney, who has a passion for science fiction and imagination, are neighbours and best friends. They both befriend the new kid on their street, Jet Propulsion, whose family members happen to be aliens! Together, they embark on great adventures, exploring the solar system, learning about space and science, but always back just in time for dinner!

programme.title: Tree Fu Tom
programme.desc: Visit the enchanted kingdom located in a tree in our hero, Tom's, backyard. Tom is blessed with the magic movement power of "tree fu" which transforms him into a "treeling" and he is transported to Treetopolis. There, along with his friends Twigs, Arilea and Zigzoo, he revels in adventures and mishaps often involving the troublesome Mushas who enjoy causing chaos for their neighbours. Tom usually has to rely on the help of the viewer to save the day as they perform their own "tree fu" moves and transfer the magic through the screen. As well as providing social development benefits to children, the show specifically encourages the kids to partake in therapeutic movements involving sweeping arms, stomping feet, and the clenching and relaxing of fists which keep kids engaged and physically active.

programme.desc: Sean, who has an all-consuming drive for science facts, and Sydney, who has a passion for science fiction and imagination, are neighbours and best friends. They both befriend the new kid on their street, Jet Propulsion, whose family members happen to be aliens! Together, they embark on great adventures, exploring the solar system, learning about space and science, but always back just in time for dinner!

programme.title: Heidi
programme.desc: Heidi is a little girl who is full of beans. She faces many problems up in the Swiss alps whilst living with her grandfather. Heidi lights up and soothes the people and animals all around her, with her enthusiastic, generous and wonderful zest for life. This bubbly, young orphan girl will learn the priceless value of friendship and mutual respect. Follow her journey as she discovers life's ups and downs.

programme.title: Peppa Pig
programme.desc: Adorable Peppa Pig is admired not only by kids but also by adults all over the world. Peppa lives together with her family, George Pig-her little brother, Mummy Pig and Daddy Pig. Peppa likes to jump in muddy puddles and play with her best friend Suzy Ship. George is too small, he barely talks, he never separates from his toy dinosaur. Mummy Pig and Daddy Pig are loving and caring parents, they go to work every day. Whether they're playing games, going to the playground or visiting their cousins, Peppa and her family are there to educate on everything life-related.
